definition.value: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a filopodium.
The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a microvillus.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a receptor for gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH), a peptide hormone that is synthesized and released by the hypothalamus and is responsible for the release of follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) and luteinizing hormone (LH) from the anterior pituitary.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a receptor for thyrotropin-releasing hormone, a tripeptide hormone that is produced by the hypothalamus and stimulates the release of thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) and prolactin by the anterior pituitary.
A protein complex that consists of an RNA 5' triphosphatase and a guanyl transferase (Cet1p and Ceg1p in S. cerevisiae -  Pct1 and Ceg1 in S. pombe) and is involved in mRNA capping.

label.value: positive regulation of exit from mitosis

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the rate of progression from anaphase|telophase (high mitotic CDK activity) to G1 (low mitotic CDK activity).
Catalysis of the reaction -  peptidyl L-proline + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- peptidyl hydroxy-L-proline + succinate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  peptidyl L-proline + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- peptidyl trans-3-hydroxy-L-proline + succinate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  peptidyl L-proline + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- peptidyl trans-4-hydroxy-L-proline + succinate + CO2.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the brain-derived neurotrophic factor receptor.
Catalysis of the cyclization of (S)-2,3-epoxysqualene to form a triterpene.
Protein complex that has a role in determining cell polarity, found at the neck of a fungal bud before and during cytokinesis.
Protein complex that has a role in determining cell polarity, found at the tip of a growing fungal bud.
Protein complex that has a role in determining cell polarity, found at the tip of a growing fungal hypha.
Protein complex that has a role in determining cell polarity, found at the tip of the mating projection in unicellular fungi exposed to mating pheromone.
A mitotic cell cycle checkpoint that detects a defect in cytokinesis and negatively regulates G2|M transition.

The cell cycle process in which the contractile ring is maintained in response to the cytokinesis checkpoint -  that is when cytokinesis is delayed awaiting completion of nuclear division or the correct formation of cytokinetic structures. This process occurs in the context of cytokinesis that takes place as part of a cell cycle.
The mitotic cell cycle checkpoint that delays or arrests cell cycle progression until cells have reached a critical size.
A mitotic cell cycle checkpoint that monitors cell size, and negatively regulates cell cycle progression between G1 and S phase until a critical size is reached.
A cell cycle checkpoint that monitors cell size, and negatively regulates cell cycle progression between G2 and M phase until a critical size is reached.

A cell cycle process that controls cell cycle progression in response to changes in DNA structure by monitoring the integrity of the DNA. The DNA integrity checkpoint begins with detection of DNA damage, defects in DNA structure or DNA replication, and progresses through signal transduction and ends with cell cycle effector processes.
A mitotic cell cycle checkpoint that detects and negatively regulates progression through the G1|S transition of the cell cycle in response to DNA damage.
A cell cycle checkpoint that detects and negatively regulates progression from G2 to M phase in the cell cycle in response to DNA damage.
A mitotic cell cycle checkpoint that slows DNA synthesis in response to DNA damage by the prevention of new origin firing and the stabilization of slow replication fork progression.
A cell cycle checkpoint that originates from the mitotic or meiotic spindle.
A cell cycle checkpoint that monitors and signals errors in the placement or orientation of the spindle in the cell. This delays the completion of anaphase until errors are corrected.

label.value: replication fork arrest at rDNA repeats

definition.value: A process that impedes the progress of the DNA replication fork at natural replication fork pausing sites within the eukaryotic rDNA repeat spacer.
A protein complex that possesses AMP-dependent protein kinase activity.
An amorphous structure surrounding the core of the centrosome, from which microtubules are nucleated -  contains gamma-tubulin.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a polymer of ubiqutin.

The junction between the axon of a motor neuron and a muscle fiber. In response to the arrival of action potentials, the presynaptic button releases molecules of neurotransmitters into the synaptic cleft. These diffuse across the cleft and transmit the signal to the postsynaptic membrane of the muscle fiber, leading to a change in post-synaptic potential.
A proteasome found in the nucleus of a cell.
A proteasome found in the endoplasmic reticulum of a cell.
A proteasome complex found in the cytosol of a cell.
The regulatory subcomplex of a proteasome located in the nucleus of a cell.
The regulatory subcomplex of a proteasome located in the endoplasmic reticulum of a cell.

A multisubunit complex located in the cytosol of a cell, which caps one or both ends of the proteasome core complex. This complex recognizes, unfolds ubiquitinated proteins and translocates them to the proteasome core complex.
The core complex of a proteasome located in the nucleus of a cell.
The core complex of a proteasome located in the endoplasmic reticulum of a cell.
The core complex of a proteasome located in the cytosol of a cell.

definition.value: The subunits forming the outer ring of the core complex of a proteasome located in the nucleus of a cell.

label.value: ER proteasome core complex, alpha-subunit complex

definition.value: The subunits forming the outer ring of the core complex of a proteasome located in the endoplasmic reticulum of a cell.

label.value: cytosolic proteasome core complex, alpha-subunit complex

definition.value: The proteasome core subcomplex that constitutes the two outer rings of the cytosolic proteasome core complex.

label.value: nuclear proteasome core complex, beta-subunit complex

definition.value: The subunits forming the inner ring of the core complex of a proteasome located in the nucleus of a cell.

label.value: ER proteasome core complex, beta-subunit complex

definition.value: The subunits forming the inner ring of the core complex of a proteasome located in the endoplasmic reticulum of a cell.

label.value: cytosolic proteasome core complex, beta-subunit complex

definition.value: The proteasome core subcomplex that constitutes the two inner rings of the cytosolic proteasome core complex.

label.value: nuclear proteasome regulatory particle, base subcomplex

definition.value: The subunits of the regulatory particle that directly associate with the core complex of a proteasome located in the nucleus of a cell.

label.value: ER proteasome regulatory particle, base subcomplex

definition.value: The subunits of the regulatory particle that directly associate with the core complex of a proteasome located in the endoplasmic reticulum of a cell.

label.value: cytosolic proteasome regulatory particle, base subcomplex

definition.value: The subcomplex of the proteasome regulatory particle that directly associates with the proteasome core complex located in the cytosol of the cell.

label.value: nuclear proteasome regulatory particle, lid subcomplex

definition.value: The subunits that form the peripheral lid of the regulatory particle of a proteasome located in the nucleus of a cell.
